Siya Kolisi (L) and the Springbok squad have been training in France. AFP/Julien de Rosa JOHANNESBURG - Siya Kolisi and Lusanda Dumke won big at the SA Rugby Player Awards. The Springbok captain walked away with the award for Player of the Year for 2021. The popular captain was able to get the most votes for his performances during a tough season. Kolisi beat teammates Lukhanyo Am, Damian de Allende, Eben Etzebeth and Makazole Mapimpi. WATCH: Siya Kolisi in his own words Sharks player Aphelele Fassi was rewarded for his amazing performances which underline his potential. He scooped the Young Player of the Year award. The Springbok Women's Player of the Year is Lusanda Dumke. The Border star was earlier also named Provincial Women's Player of the Year.